&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Paediatric Community Dietitian Jobshare&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Grade: Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: Nutrition &amp; Dietetics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Queen Mary’s Hospital, Roehampton&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jobshare considered  for 15 to 22.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Band 6 Paediatric Community Dietitian to join our community dietetics team. We are advertising this post as a job share. We are looking for a candidate who wants to work part time. The hours are flexible, to combine with the existing postholder who is returning from maternity leave. You will be based at Queen Mary’s Hospital in Roehampton, Southwest London, covering the area of Wandsworth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as a member of a friendly team, with responsibility for a varied community paediatrics caseload including home enteral tube feeding, special needs children and allergy. You will work in many different community settings including outpatients services, health centres, special schools and patients own homes. You may also work remotely as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supervised and fully supported by a full-time Band 7 Specialist Paediatric Community Dietitian and will also work closely with the acute Paediatric Dietitians within St George’s Hospital. Previous experience in the community is desirable, though not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CPD is well supported for all staff members within the department and we participate in student training with St George’s Hospital. If you enjoy a challenge, work well as part of a team and have good communication, interpersonal and organisational skills, we hope you will apply. You will be required to travel around Wandsworth to undertake the duties of the post; car or bicycle user is desirable but public transport is an option.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Amy Guppy: Specialist Paediatric Community Dietitian &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
